<item>
            <title>[LU-1538] cleanup test scripts</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1538</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are a number of issues with running test scripts on a single-node system.&lt;br/&gt;
Several minor cleanups to the test scripts are also possible (coding style, more clear output, etc):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;sanity.sh test_51ba() should clean up subdirectories even if test_51b() failed&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;sanity.sh test_61ic() shouldn&apos;t print all files to stdout&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Implement acceptance-small.sh via auster, so that we don&apos;t have to maintain two separate test wrappers, and it would be possible for users running acc-sm to upload results to Maloo.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
